					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">WedNESday wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Don't forget using the PPU's VRAM ($0000-1FFF) gives you almost direct access to the video buffer. If you set the 960 tiles to 0, 1, 2, 3, 4 etc. in the pattern table then you have 2-bit colour access.</div>
<br />
<br />The trouble is, the PPU can only address 256 background tiles - if you want to use more per screen, you need to either do carefully timed bank switches OR use the MMC5 (which generally also restricts you to CHR ROM).</div>

					
